race.comment: CAPE LEEUWIN (3) jumped a 100-1 chance in the Placid Ark Prelude 11 days ago and finished well back when first-up. He's right back in grade today which is a big positive for him and he should have taken plenty of improvement from that performance. Can bounce back to his best now. MAALIS SONG (4) was a little slow to begin, but mowed down his rivals impressively first-up when the race favourite. Goes from a Maiden to a CL3, but rates highly on that effort with upside and improvement expected. Can go on with the job. NINE BALL (5) was trending the right way before a 3.4L defeat when favourite in Saturday grade 53 days ago. Back in trip off a freshen, but CJP remains in the saddle from a good gate and she can put her best foot forward. RALLY THE TROOPS (2) looks set for a bold first-up effort on the back of a nice trial recently. PAT'S LAST BANG (8) is racing well and is not to be discounted.
